Outputs #!T,1,161,321,646  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--14*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   #!N TAB Name TAB Type TAB Description 
#!EF #!N TAB output TAB color field TAB renderable positions of 
input field #!N TAB - TAB - TAB #!EF #!N #!N 
Functional Details #!N #!N This module creates an output field that 
shows the positions of a specified input. #!N #!I0 #!N #!N 
#!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   input #!EF #!EF #!I50 #!N specifies the 
object whose positions are to be shown. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   every #!EF #!EF #!I50 #!N determines the relative number of 
input positions shown in the output. By default, all positions are 
shown. #!N #!N The multiplicand used is the reciprocal of the 
parameter value (e.g., given a value of 2, the output shows 
half the positions in the input). #!I0 #!N #!N #!N #!N 
#!I0 #!N Notes: #!N #!I30 #!N 1. If the input object 
lacks a "colors" component, the module adds a default color to 
the output. #!N #!I30 #!N 2. Position-dependent color and data components 
are passed to the output. #!I0 #!N #!N #!N #!N Components 
#!N #!N Adds a "colors" component if the input does not 
already have one. All input components, except "connections," are propagated to 
the output. Invalid positions are not passed through to the output. 
